on past behavior

15:53.387 --> 15:56.999
and Andi pointed out
that people can change.

15:57.043 --> 15:59.697
So, I wanted
to look you in the eye

15:59.741 --> 16:02.570
and tell you I'm sorry.

16:02.613 --> 16:04.180
Thank you.

16:04.224 --> 16:05.703
That really means a lot.

16:05.747 --> 16:08.532
Good. A-And, and I hope
we can put all this

16:08.576 --> 16:10.360
behind us and start fresh.

16:10.404 --> 16:11.796
Of course.

16:11.840 --> 16:13.363
We're family.

16:13.407 --> 16:16.105
We're gonna be
in each other's lives forever.

16:16.149 --> 16:17.977
And it's just nice
to think that

16:18.020 --> 16:21.197
when I sit across from you
at Thanksgiving,

16:21.241 --> 16:23.373
I will know...

16:23.417 --> 16:25.419
that I owned you.

16:29.249 --> 16:30.424
What?

16:30.467 --> 16:33.514
I got to admit,
you were tough.

16:33.557 --> 16:35.864
I knew after
the intervention

16:35.907 --> 16:38.736
that you were the only one
that wouldn't buy the new me.

16:38.780 --> 16:40.695
I haven't changed at all.

16:40.738 --> 16:44.264
In fact, I'm probably
a little worse.

16:46.831 --> 16:48.094
So I was right.

16:48.137 --> 16:51.053
Yeah, but I got you
acting so crazy

16:51.097 --> 16:53.360
